93 (b)(1) Not later than January 1, 2027, the department
94 shall adopt rules that provide for the beneficial reuse of
95 foundry sand. The rules shall provide that foundry sand may be
96 used for any of the following:
97 a. Raw material in the manufacture of asphalt, cement,
98 and concrete products.
99 b. Subbase for hard-surface road construction.
100 c. Fill Material.
101 d. Filler for sandbags used for emergency flood
102 control.
103 e. Leachate control drainage material at sanitary
104 landfills.
105 f. Alternative cover material at sanitary landfills.
106 g. Other uses that provide a functional benefit and are
107 substitutes for the use of a virgin material that must be
108 otherwise obtained.
109 (2) For purposes of this subsection, the term "foundry
110 sand" means spent green molding sand, resin bonded molding
111 sand, or core sand with primary components consisting of
112 combinations of silica sand, bentonite clay, and carbonaceous
Page 4

combinations of silica sand, bentonite clay, and carbonaceous
